{
  "texts": [
    "Donors have received no compensation for participating in this study.",
    "Isolation of human liver cells from fresh tissue.",
    "Isolation of the primary human hepatocytes (PHH) and non-parenchymal cells (NPC) from the liver tissue was performed as described previously 49.",
    "Briefly, PHH and NPC were isolated from the same tissue sample simultaneously by a two-step EDTA/collagenase perfusion technique and then purified by Percoll density gradient centrifugation.",
    "To obtain different cell types from NPC fraction, this cell suspension underwent two different centrifugation steps: 300 g for 5 min to get liver endothelial cells, mesenchymal cells and Kupffer cells; 650 g for 7 min to get the majority of Kupffer cells."
  ]
}